The build is successful, the container starts, but the logs show an error, and the service is not available on the `PORT` specified in the config (env):

```
send          | {"Timestamp":1577862561126000000,"Logger":"FirefoxSend","Type":"uncaughtException","Severity":0,"Pid":1,"EnvVersion":"2.0","Fields":{"error":"Error: ENOENT: no such file or directory, open '/app/node_modules/fxa-geodb/db/cities-db.mmdb'","stack":"\n    at Object.openSync (fs.js:443:3)\n    at Object.readFileSync (fs.js:343:35)\n    at Object.exports.openSync (/app/node_modules/maxmind/index.js:50:30)\n    at module.exports (/app/node_modules/fxa-geodb/lib/fxa-geodb.js:16:28)\n    at Object.<anonymous> (/app/server/amplitude.js:2:35)\n    at Module._compile (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:778:30)\n    at Object.Module._extensions..js (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:789:10)\n    at Module.load (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:653:32)\n    at tryModuleLoad (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:593:12)\n    at Function.Module._load (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:585:3)"}}
```

Although the geoip invocation is in a try-catch statement itself, the module load is not, so the app crashes: https://github.com/mozilla/send/blob/master/server/amplitude.js#L25-L29

The quickest fix is to comment out this line, then rebuild the image, it works fine then:
https://github.com/mozilla/send/blob/master/server/amplitude.js#L2

```javascript
// const geoip = require('fxa-geodb')();
```
